B%20Chris%20LaCivita%2C%20one%20of%20Trump's%20co-campaign%20managers%2C%20wrote%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223e20286a-a899-4976-b5fa-55b0541b6f22%5C%22%3EKamala%20Harris%20is%20not%20going%20back%20to%202020.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20her%20sprint%20to%20the%20nomination%2C%20Harris%20has%20jettisoned%20many%20of%20the%20progressive%20policies%20that%20defined%20her%202020%20primary%20campaign.%20Addressing%20one%20of%20her%20biggest%20potential%20weaknesses%2C%20Harris%20reiterated%20her%20support%20for%20the%20bipartisan%20Senate%20immigration%20plan%2C%20which%20is%20the%20most%20conservative%20immigration%20policy%20Democrats%20have%20supported%20in%20decades.%20Even%20some%20Senate%20Republicans%20blamed%20Trump%20for%20killing%20that%20deal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell%2C%20I%20refuse%20to%20play%20politics%20with%20our%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20said.%20%26quot%3BHere%20is%20my%20pledge%20to%20you%3A%20As%20President%2C%20I%20will%20bring%20back%20the%20bipartisan%20border%20security%20bill%20that%20he%20killed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20Harris%20was%20among%20a%20handful%20of%20candidates%20during%20the%202020%20primary%20season%20who%20expressed%20support%20for%20decriminalizing%20the%20act%20itself%20of%20crossing%20a%20border%20illegally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFellow%20Democrats%20are%20cheering%20on%20her%20reinvention%20even%20as%20Republicans%20try%20to%20brand%20her%20as%20a%20flip-flooper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20district%2C%20I%20say%20what%20works%20in%20Michigan%20works%20in%20San%20Francisco%20what%20works%20in%20Francisco%20might%20not%20work%20in%20Michigan%2C%26quot%3B%20Pelosi%20told%20Politico%20in%20an%20interview%20on%20the%20sidelines.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20we%20must%20win%20Michigan.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPennslyvania%20Gov.%20Josh%20Shapiro%2C%20who%20Harris%20considered%20a%20possible%20running%20mate%2C%20praised%20the%20vice%20president%20for%20reversing%20her%202020%20view%20that%