-bags-so-hard-to-recycle-2024-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Pentagon%20knew%20about%20the%20gearbox%20failure%2010%20years%20before%20it%20caused%20the%20deadliest%20V-22%20crash%20in%20Air%20Force%20history%2C%20docs%20show%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20front%20view%20of%20a%20US%20Marine%20Corps%20MV-22%20Osprey%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664b8c7c20abc1efe8fba689%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20US%20Marine%20Corps%20MV-22%20Osprey%20conducts%20its%20flight%20demonstration%20during%20an%20air%20show%20in%20North%20Carolina.%3Cp%3EUS%20Marine%20Corps%20photo%20by%20Lance%20Cpl.%20Matthew%20Williams%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20gearbox%20defect%20that%20caused%20the%20V-22%20crash%20in%202023%20had%20been%20found%20as%20early%20as%202013%2C%20reports%20show.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBut%20a%20top%20Air%20Force%20official%20said%20the%20fatal%20Osprey%20crash%20was%20the%20first%20time%20the%20gearbox%20part%20failed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20Pentagon%20was%20warned%20about%20the%20flaw%20in%202014%2C%20but%20it%20seemingly%20went%20unaddressed%2C%20a%20probe%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EInternal%20safety%20documents%20obtained%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20show%20that%20warnings%20related%20to%20a%20mechanical%20issue%20that%20caused%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fair-force%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAir%20Force%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fequipment%2Fcv-22-osprey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EOsprey%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdaily-news%2F2024%2F08%2F07%2Fpilots-family-members-say-crew-being-unfairly-blamed-novembers-deadly-air-force-osprey-crash.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ecrash%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Japan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%2C%20killing%20eight%20airmen%2C%20had%20been%20identified%20as%20far%20back%20as%202013%20but%20seemingly%20went%20unaddressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20investigation%20released%20earlier%20this%20month%20by%20the%20Air%20Force%20pointed%20to%20an%20issue%20in%20the%20controversial%20tilt-rotor%20aircraft's%20prop%20rotor%20gearbox%20as%20a%20cause%20of%20the%20November%2029%20crash.%20Specifically%2C%20the%20service%20identified%20a%20single%20high-speed%20planetary%20pinion%20gear%20that%20had%20fractured.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20an%20internal%20Safety%20Investigation%20Board%20report%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20not%20been%20made%20public%20%E2%80%94%20showed%20that%20other%20gears%20in%20that%20gearbox%20similarly%20failed%20in%202013%20and%20warnings%20related%20to%20that%20part%20failure%20were%20brought%20to%20the%20Pentagon%20a%20year%20later.%20Plus%2C%20serious%20manufacturing%20issues%20plagued%20the%20components%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Osprey%2C%20call%20sign%20Gundam%2022%2C%20was%20on%20an%20Air%20Force%20Special%20Operations%20Command%20training%20mission%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20Island%2C%20Japan.%20As%20the%20single%20gear%20began%20to%20shred%2C%20it%20sent%20debris%20throughout%20the%20gearbox%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20began%20to%20fail%20and%20caused%20the%20left%20proprotor%20to%20stop%20operating.%20The%20aircraft%20then%20fell%20out%20of%20the%20sky.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20the%20deadliest%20CV-22B%20crash%20in%20the%20Air%20Force's%20history%2C%20claiming%20the%20lives%20of%20Maj.%20Jeffrey%20T.%20Hoernemann%3B%20Maj.%20Eric%20V.%20Spendlove%3B%20Maj.%20Luke%20A.%20Unrath%3B%20Capt.%20Terrell%20K.%20Brayman%3B%20Tech.%20Sgt.%20Zachary%20E.%20Lavoy%3B%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Jake%20M.%20Turnage%3B%20Senior%20Airman%20Brian%20K.%20Johnson%3B%20and%20Staff%20Sgt.%20Jake%20Galliher.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224830299a-a2e7-42d9-ae83-53b4176c652d%5C%22%3EHistory%20of%20gear%20defects%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Debris%20believed%20to%20be%20from%20a%20US%20military%20Osprey%20aircraft%20is%20seen%20in%20waters%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20Island.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66ac0ecab4912df3ae1864f6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDebris%20believed%20to%20be%20from%20a%20US%20military%20Osprey%20aircraft%20is%20seen%20in%20waters%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Yakushima%20Island.%3Cp%3EJapan%20Coast%20Guard%20via%20AP%2C%20File%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20Air%20Force's%20public%20report%2C%20called%20an%20Accident%20Investigation%20Board%20or%20AIB%2C%20and%20its%20internal%20Safety%20Investigation%20Board%2C%20or%20SIB%2C%20reports%20into%20the%20crash%20agree%20that%20Gundam%2022%20was%20brought%20down%20by%20the%20fracturing%20of%20a%20single%20gear%20%E2%80%94%20a%20high-speed%20planetary%20pinion%20gear%20%E2%80%94%20into%20five%20large%20pieces%2C%20which%20caused%20other%20failures%20in%20the%20proprotor%20gearbox.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reports%20also%20go%20on%20to%20fault%20the%20Air%20Force%20Special%20Operations%20Command%20crew%20for%20not%20heeding%20the%20warning%20lights%20even%20though%2C%20according%20to%20members%20of%20the%20Osprey%20community%2C%20the%20warnings%20the%20crew%20received%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdaily-news%2F2024%2F08%2F07%2Fpilots-family-members-say-crew-being-unfairly-blamed-novembers-deadly-air-force-osprey-crash.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Econsidered%20common%20and%20the%20community%20often%20saw%20them%20as%20just%20part%20of%20the%20aircraft's%20operation%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20internal%20safety%20report%20found%20that%20the%20high-speed%20gear%20that%20failed%20on%20Gundam%2022%20because%20of%20a%20single%20crack%20was%20%26quot%3Bsimilar%20to%20those%20seen%20on%20seven%20previous%20failures%20in%20low-speed%20planetary%20pinion%20gears.%26quot%3B%20The%20two%20sets%20of%20gears%20sit%20next%20to%20each%20other%20in%20the%20gearbox%20and%20are%20made%20from%20the%20same%20alloy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20notes%20that%20in%20all%20the%20other%20instances%2C%20the%20Ospreys%20landed%20before%20the%20gear%20failed%20completely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20analysis%20showed%20that%20five%20of%20those%20prior%20failures%2C%20which%20go%20back%20to%202013%2C%20were%20caused%20by%20%26quot%3Bnon-metallic%20inclusions%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20defect%20in%20the%20metal%20alloy%20from%20which%20the%20gears%20were%20made.%20Air%20Force%20investigators%20say%20that%20Gundam%2022's%20gear%20also%20cracked%20%26quot%3Bmost%20likely%20due%20to%20non-metallic%20material%20inclusion.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223100%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22V-22%20Osprey%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e7d792c92e19135060a9313%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222064%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Navy%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%2C%20given%20the%20rate%20at%20which%20those%20inclusions%20were%20making%20it%20into%20the%20alloy%20used%20in%20the%20gears%2C%20a%20failure%20such%20as%20the%20one%20Gundam%2022%20experienced%20was%20bound%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20number%20of%20failures%20in%20low-speed%20planetary%20pinion%20gears%20will%20have%20a%20similar%20ratio%20to%20high-speed%20planetary%20pinion%20gears%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Air%20Force%20investigators%20wrote%20before%20noting%20that%20given%20%26quot%3Bfive%20such%20failures%20in%20low-speed%20planetary%20pinion%20gears%2C%20...%20one%20failure%20in%20the%20high-speed%20planetary%20pinion%20gear%20can%20be%20expected.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20the%20Joint%20Program%20Office%2C%20which%20oversees%20the%20Osprey%20program%20for%20the%20Pentagon%2C%20was%20sent%20a%20formal%20risk%20assessment%20titled%20%26quot%3BGear%20Metal%20Raw%20Material%20Impurities%26quot%3B%20by%20Bell%20Textron%20and%20Boeing%2C%20the%20companies%20that%20build%20the%20Osprey.%20But%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Air%20Force%20internal%20investigation%2C%20the%20notice%20%26quot%3Bdid%20not%20adequately%20assess%20the%20risk%20of%20high-speed%20gear%20failure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20also%20found%20that%20there%20was%20no%20testing%20of%20the%20high-speed%20gears%20done%20at%20the%20time%2C%20which%20meant%20there%20wasn't%20an%20%26quot%3Badequate%20understanding%20of%20the%20failure%20that%20occurred%20in%20this%20mishap.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20Osprey%20program%20office%20%E2%80%94%20part%20of%20Naval%20Air%20Systems%20Command%2C%20or%20NAVAIR%20%E2%80%94%20received%20the%20notice%20in%202014%2C%20it%20did%20not%20fully%20process%20it%20to%20determine%20whether%20the%20risks%20it%20outlined%20would%20just%20be%20accepted%20by%20the%20military%20or%20somehow%20mitigated.%20It%20is%20not%20clear%20from%20the%20Air%20Force%20investigation%20why%20that%20did%20not%20occur.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20report%20found%20that%20%26quot%3BNAVAIR%20implemented%20contractual%20financial%20withholds%20in%20hope%20the%20contractor%20would%20correct%20deficiencies%20in%20the%20%5Balloy%5D%20processing%20that%20had%20resulted%20in%20previous%20gear%20failures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20contractor%20%E2%80%94%20Universal%20Stainless%20%E2%80%94%20made%20the%20alloy%20that%20later%20failed%20in%20Gundam%2022%20and%2C%20since%202014%2C%20has%20supplied%20%26quot%3Ba%20significant%20proportion%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20alloy%20used%20in%20the%20Osprey%20gearboxes%20that%20are%20now%20under%20scrutiny.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20since%20that%20Bell-Boeing%20risk%20assessment%20was%20issued%20in%202014%2C%20Air%20Force%20investigators%20found%20that%20%26quot%3Bthere%20have%20continued%20to%20be%20inclusion%20failures%20in%20%5Balloy%5D%2C%20suggesting%20contractual%20financial%20withholds%20did%20not%20prompt%20corrective%20actions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20flying%20US%20Navy%20Bell-Boeing%20V-22%20Osprey.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65713df87a3c8094d5da7fc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224873%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20flying%20US%20Navy%20Bell-Boeing%20V-22%20Osprey.%3Cp%3EBernd%20von%20Jutrczenka%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20reached%20out%20to%20Bell%20Flight%2C%20the%20point%20of%20contact%20for%20questions%20regarding%20the%20V-22%2C%20for%20comment%20but%20did%20not%20receive%20a%20reply%20in%20time%20for%20publication.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20specifically%20asked%20the%20Joint%20Program%20Office%20whether%20NAVAIR%20still%20stands%20by%20its%20choice%20to%20use%20a%20financial%20approach%20as%20a%20way%20to%20handle%20substandard%20materials%20in%20V-22%20component%20manufacturing%20or%20if%20Universal%20Stainless%20still%20makes%20parts%20for%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20program%20office%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJJ%20Gertler%2C%20an%20aviation%20analyst%20and%20expert%20with%20the%20Teal%20Group%2C%20told%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0in%20an%20interview%20that%20such%20an%20approach%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20unusual%26quot%3B%20but%20said%2C%20ultimately%2C%20the%20aircraft%20was%20approved%20to%20be%20received%20at%20the%20end%20of%20those%20negotiations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20progress%20payments%20that%20go%20on%20during%20the%20course%20of%20a%20contract.%20It's%20not%20that%20they%20get%20all%20the%20money%20at%20the%20beginning%20or%20the%20end%2C%20and%20those%20progress%20payments%20are%20often%20withheld%20or%20modified%20until%20certain%20criteria%20are%20met%20like%20you've%20got%20to%20hit%20this%20standard%20on%20that%20part%20or%20this%20amount%20of%20durability%2C%26quot%3B%20Gertler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUltimately%2C%20he%20said%2C%20somebody%20approved%20the%20aircraft%20to%20be%20received%20by%20the%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2233302079-25ce-4d07-8ab5-b075460eca95%5C%22%3EJoint%20Program%20Office%20role%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20logo%20is%20affixed%20to%20a%20podium%20ahead%20of%20a%20press%20conference%20at%20the%20Pentagon.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c77ffbc72ebc54a40e1078%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20Department%20of%20Defense%20logo%20is%20affixed%20to%20a%20podium%20ahead%20of%20a%20press%20conference%20at%20the%20Pentagon.%3Cp%3ECelal%20Gunes%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20the%20public%20report%20on%20the%20deadly%20crash%20in%20Japan%20was%20also%20a%20suggestion%20that%20the%20Joint%20Program%20Office%20had%20a%20role%20to%20play%20in%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAir%20Force%20investigators%20found%20%26quot%3Bthat%20inadequate%20action%20at%20the%20program%20level%20and%20inadequate%20coordination%20between%20the%20program%20office%20and%20the%20services%20prevented%20comprehensive%20awareness%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20risks%20of%20the%20failures%20within%20the%20gearbox%20and%20%26quot%3Bsubstantially%20contributed%20to%20the%20mishap.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20public%20report%20does%20not%20offer%20further%20detail%20about%20what%20actions%20the%20Osprey%20program%20office%20should%20have%20taken%2C%20the%20internal%20report%20shows%20that%20it%20was%20aware%20of%20at%20least%20five%20instances%20of%20gear%20failures%20on%20the%20low-speed%20side%20of%20the%20same%20gearbox%20that%20was%20at%20fault%20in%20the%20Gundam%2022%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Osprey%20program%20office%20with%20nearly%20a%20dozen%20questions%20stemming%20from%20our%20review%20of%20the%20internal%20Air%20Force%20report%2C%20but%20officials%20declined%20to%20comment%20specifically%20on%20the%20safety%20investigation%20board%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20Air%20Force%20Safety%20Center%20spokesman%20declined%20to%20authenticate%20parts%20of%20the%20document%2C%20citing%20%26quot%3Bthe%20integrity%20of%20the%20information%20that%20may%20come%20from%20it.%26quot%3B%20The%20documents%20obtained%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20marked%20%26quot%3BControlled%20Unclassified%20Information%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20label%20used%20for%20nonsecret%20but%20internal%20information%20that%20the%20government%20wants%20to%20keep%20out%20of%20public%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSafety%20investigations%20are%20highly%20effective%20because%20of%20their%20inward-facing%2C%20limited-use%20analysis%2C%20and%20follow-up%20action%2C%20a%20product%20of%20military%20safety%20privilege%2C%26quot%3B%20Keith%20Wright%2C%20a%20spokesman%20for%20the%20Air%20Force%20Safety%20Center%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20month.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Accident%20Investigation%20Board%20is%20the%20official%20release%20mechanism%20for%20accident%20information.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20details%20about%20previous%20gear%20failures%20in%20the%20Osprey%20also%20cast%20doubt%20on%20the%20statements%20and%20assurances%20of%20top%20NAVAIR%20officials%20who%20claimed%20the%20issue%20that%20brought%20down%20Gundam%2022%20had%20not%20been%20encountered%20before%20or%20seemingly%20came%20out%20of%20left%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVice%20Adm.%20Carl%20Chebi%2C%20the%20head%20of%20NAVAIR%2C%20which%20oversees%20all%20V-22%20operations%20across%20the%20military%2C%20said%20during%20a%20June%2012%20congressional%20hearing%20on%20Osprey%20safety%20%26quot%3Bthat%20data%20was%20presented%20to%20myself%20that%20indicated%20that%20the%20platform%20had%20experienced%20a%20catastrophic%20material%20failure%20that%20we%20have%20never%20seen%20before%20in%20the%20V-22%20program.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225797%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20hat%20of%20a%20member%20of%20the%20U.S.%20Navy%20sits%20on%20a%20chair%20in%20the%20Hart%20Senate%20Office%20Building.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66c77f0fc72ebc54a40e100f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223865%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20hat%20of%20a%20member%20of%20the%20U.S.%20Navy%20sits%20on%20a%20chair%20in%20the%20Hart%20Senate%20Office%20Building.%3Cp%3EDrew%20Angerer%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENAVAIR%20and%20the%20V-22's%20Joint%20Program%20Office%20did%20not%20return%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20asking%20them%20to%20clarify%20Chebi's%20comments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPast%20indications%20about%20possible%20safety%20issues%20with%20the%20gearbox%20were%20also%20not%20fully%20communicated%20to%20those%20flying%20and%20maintaining%20the%20aircraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Heyse%2C%20a%20spokeswoman%20for%20the%20Air%20Force's%20Special%20Operations%20Command%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20citing%20the%20public%20accident%20report%20findings%20%E2%80%94%20that%20NAVAIR%20has%20done%20safety%20assessments%20on%20the%20gearbox%20and%20said%20those%20analyses%20found%20%26quot%3Bfailure%20to%20be%20remote%20or%20improbable%20but%20also%20indicated%20that%20total%20loss%20of%20aircraft%20and%20crew%20were%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHeyse%20added%20that%20program-wide%20changes%2C%20such%20as%20advising%20less%20risky%20responses%20in%20certain%20situations%2C%20%26quot%3Bwere%20not%20always%20implemented%2C%20or%20were%20implemented%20in%20a%20manner%20that%20did%20not%20stress%20the%20severity%20of%20the%20risk.%26quot%3B%20She%20noted%20that%20aircrew%20training%20on%20how%20to%20react%20to%20gearbox%20indications%20wasn't%20modified%20and%20that%20the%20findings%20%26quot%3Bwere%20not%20always%20communicated%20to%20the%20military%20services%2C%20limiting%20opportunities%20for%20service-specific%20changes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FMilitary.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMilitary.com%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.military.com%2Fdaily-news%2F2024%2F08%2F01%2Fair-force-investigation-finds-gearbox-failure-downed-osprey-off-japan-coast.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ereported%20earlier%20this%20month%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20AFSOC%20has%20now%20changed%20some%20of%20its%20protocols%20for%20aircrews%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20crash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChebi%20has%20previously%20said%20that%20he%20doesn't%20expect%20the%20V-22%20to%20be%20fully%20operational%20again%20until%20at%20least%20%26quot%3Bmid-2025.%26quot%3B%20But%20Lt.%20Gen.%20Michael%20Conley%2C%20the%20head%20of%20Air%20Force%20Special%20Operations%20Command%2C%20told%20reporters%20earlier%20this%20month%20he%20hopes%20to%20be%20supporting%20combatant%20commanders%20with%20the%20Air