what%20ableist%2C%20particularly%20from%20a%20disability-focused%20perspective%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sweta%20muses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20typical%20image%20of%20a%20stand-up%20comedian%20involves%20a%20performer%20standing%20on%20stage%2C%20which%20can%20be%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20accessibility-centred%20narrative%20we%20strive%20for%20today.%20Generally%2C%20people%20with%20disabilities%20are%20imagined%20working%20from%20home%20or%2C%20if%20they%E2%80%99re%20comedians%2C%20performing%20on%20Zoom%20or%20writing%20funny%20blogs.%20Choosing%20to%20perform%20stand-up%20comedy%20in%20person%20is%20in%20itself%20a%20rebellious%20act%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeing%20the%20only%20Indian%20stand-up%20comedian%20with%20spina%20bifida%20has%20made%20Sweta%20aware%20that%20her%20comedy%20has%20a%20deeper%20purpose%3A%20to%20shed%20light%20on%20the%20issues%20confronting%20people%20with%20disabilities%20and%20to%20ask%20her%20audience%20to%20think%20more%20deeply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Mandar%20Latkar%2C%20a%20peer%20in%20the%20stand-up%20comedy%20scene%20who%20has%20witnessed%20her%20craft%20up%20close%2C%20Sweta%20excels%20at%20addressing%20tough%20issues%20with%20humour.%20%E2%80%9CSweta%20boldly%20addresses%20challenging%20themes%2C%20including%20her%20personal%20experiences%2C%E2%80%9D%20adding%20that%20she%E2%80%99s%20not%20afraid%20to%20confront%20topics%20that%20might%20have%20once%20been%20uncomfortable%20for%20her.%20He%20also%20highlights%20that%20Sweta%20wraps%20up%20her%20comedy%20sets%20with%20a%20segment%20focused%20on%20educating%20the%20audience%20about%20disability%20and%20correcting%20common%20misconceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20if%20she%20believes%20her%20voice%20has%20changed%20over%20the%20years%20to%20better%20connect%20with%20her%20audiences%2C%20she%20responds%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20my%20voice%20has%20changed%20dramatically.%E2%80%9D%20Sweta%20remains%20committed%20to